These are Puzzles for 1x4 Level 8

.:: Puzzle 1x4-Level-8-1::.
The people use 4 different means of transport: quad-bike, taxi, tram, motorbike
1. the person driving the motorbike is on the left or right of the person driving the quad-bike##3
2. the person driving the quad-bike is somewhere to the right of the person driving the motorbike##5
3. the person driving the taxi is not to the left of the person driving the tram##8
4. the person driving the taxi is on the left of the person driving the motorbike##1

.:: Answer ::.
|       |      1       |     2      |   3   |   4    |
| Transport   | tram | taxi | motorbike | quad-bike |

 #################################

 
.:: Puzzle 1x4-Level-8-2::.
The people perfer 4 different movie-genres: scientific, zombie, time-travel, sports
1. the person watching scientific movies is not to the right of the person watching sports movies##8
2. the person watching zombie movies is between the person watching sports movies and the person watching time-travel movies##2
3. the person watching zombie movies is on the left of the person watching sports movies##1
4. the person watching sports movies is somewhere to the right of the person watching scientific movies##5

.:: Answer ::.
|            |  1  |  2   |    3     |    4    |
| Movie-Genre   | scientific | time-travel | zombie | sports |

 #################################

 
.:: Puzzle 1x4-Level-8-3::.
The people prefer 4 different music-genres: d&b, salsa, trance, gospel
1. the fan of trance is somewhere to the right of the fan of salsa##5
2. the fan of d&b is on the left of the fan of gospel##1
3. the fan of salsa is not to the left of the fan of gospel##8

.:: Answer ::.
|        |    1    |   2   |   3    |   4    |
| Music-Genre   | d&b | gospel | salsa | trance |

 #################################

 
.:: Puzzle 1x4-Level-8-4::.
There are 4 different nationalities: french, dutch, australian, british
1. the british is somewhere between the french and the dutch##7
2. the british is not to the right of the australian##8
3. the australian is in an odd position##4
4. the australian is not to the right of the french##8

.:: Answer ::.
|         |   1   |      2      |       3       |   4    |
| Nationality   | dutch | british | australian | french |

